                <note rend="inline" type="source">823.00/253: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul General at Callao-Lima</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Handley</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-12T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 12, 1919</hi>, [<hi rend="italic">4
                            p.m.</hi>]</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your July 4, 3 p.m.<note n="4" xml:id="d708fn4">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_721">p. 721</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Department at a loss to understand how your private interview with Leguia came
                    about. Did you call upon him? You are instructed to ascertain from American
                    Minister the attitude of this Government toward recent events in Peru and be
                    governed accordingly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
